BTW, it's unrelated but your sample code is a bit off. I let myself correct it:

```python
class ToInject(object):
    def __init__(self, name):
        self.name=name

@api.route('/hello')
class Hello(Resource):
    @injector.inject(name=ToInject)  # <----- changed this line
    def __init__(self, name):
        self.name = name

    def get(self):
        return 'Hello {}'.format(self.name);
```

Note: since ``ToInject`` requires an argument in its constructor you need to create a provider for it and create an instance yourself (or make ``ToInject``'s constructor argument injectable).

