@miguelgrinberg the changes i made to flack to get zmq working as a message queue transport are [here](https://github.com/etseidler/flack/commits/zmq-transport-mods).

after taking another look at those changes, i'm not totally convinced that the socketio emits are now being done on a separate process. however, that was not my main goal in testing using flack. it was to demonstrate that zmq could work as a message queue transport for apps besides the one that i am working on. please let me know what you think. i know i have emits working in distinct processes within my application.

one neat thing that i did was the following: got the flack app running, stopped the zmq message broker temporarily (mainly to show that the messages really were being sent via zmq), sent a few messages from multiple clients while the broker was down, and then started the message broker up again. with zmq's implementation, those messages sent while the broker was down were not lost, but were automatically picked up and sent out to the clients once the message broker was running again. that was pretty cool to see.

