I am curious where in the documentation did you find the mention that you should be able to just say `parent = "blog"`. That is not the case and the documentation needs to be clearer about that. I am sorry it misled you.

The solution you labeled as a workaround is currently the only solution and it is the recommended way. I experimented with other ways to map meta fields, but none of them *felt* natural (no objective reasons). Settings things like parent type is easy enough as you describe it, but with more complicated stuff like defining `_all` with analyzers etc it would imho get out of hand:

    class Post(DocType):
        class Meta:
            all = {'enabled': False}
            routing = {'required': True, 'path': 'post.author.id'}

That is why I opted for the more explicit approach:

    class Post(DocType):
        class Meta:
            mapping = Mapping('post')
            mapping.meta('_all', enabled=False)
            mapping.meta('_routing', required=True, path='post.author.id')


Does this make sense? I am definitely open to suggestions, or if people think that this wouldn't be an issue I would love to hear that too.

