OK, after a while of debugging, I finally traced this to Clang's handling of infinite loops. This code
```
static void infinite_loop()
{
    while (1);
}

int main()
{
    infinite_loop();
}
```
actually causes the program to exit (with `clang -O1`), instead of entering an infinite loop!

So this is clearly a Clang bug.

