@tristanbes  Ah, I see.  It appears travis-ci doesn't support the use of system-wide package installation in their container-based workers (http://docs.travis-ci.com/user/installing-dependencies/#Installing-Ubuntu-packages).  It appears there is a container-based add-on that allows the user of `apt` (http://docs.travis-ci.com/user/apt/).  However, I don't see a similar `pip` add-on.

In the meantime, you'll either need to use `virtualenv tower-cli && ~/path/to/venv/bin/activate && pip install ansible-tower-cli && ci/release.sh`.  Or you'll have to interact with the Tower API using `curl` or the ansible `uri` module.

There appears to be another workaround offered suggested here -> https://github.com/travis-ci/travis-ci/issues/3563

