The nesting of the structures (list of services, each having a list of server), where both service and server TLV have their own data blobs is pretty annoying when it needs to be defined as a static C arrays. Namely, it suggests such structures:

```
struct ServerConfig {
   uint8_t mServerData[ 255 ];
   // ...
} 

struct ServiceConfig {
   uint8_t mServiceData[ 255 ];
   ServerConfig mServers[ 62 ];
   // ...
} 
``` 
Which causes the structure to have like 16 kilobytes. Since network data is 255 bytes max, Service TLV has minimum of 4 bytes of header, it is at most of 251 bytes per all Server TLVs, each having at least 4 bytes. So, it is not possible to have more than 62 Server TLVs. Otherwise, the whole structure would be much longer.

When used as a local network data, it is not a problem, we deal with max 1 server (current) at a time. When iterating through network data from leader, the API can't use structs like the above.

